Reasoning: The paper deals with the study of digraphs and their properties, specifically the class of bi-arc digraphs and their relationship with conservative semi-lattice polymorphisms. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithms for recognizing this class of digraphs, which falls under the scope of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of semi-lattice polymorphisms and the characterization of the class of bi-arc digraphs also involves concepts from lattice theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between bi-arc digraphs and other classes of graphs, such as interval graphs and adjusted interval digraphs, which falls under the scope of computational geometry (cs.CG).
